summary: As someone who watches an unhealthy amt of TV, equal parts police procedurals, thrillers, spy movies, plot heavy high fantasy as...
body: As someone who watches an unhealthy amt of TV, equal parts police procedurals, thrillers, spy movies, plot heavy high fantasy as well as dramedy and attempts at subversive situational comedy; im gna hafta say, in the wake of its two dimensional anti Russian undertones, overall clumsy logic, not very clear understanding of sociopathy, potential over dependency on shock value, questionable portrayal of a younger bisexual sociopath in a sexual relationship w an older, passive and inexperienced detective character, Killing Eve…. is a good comedy.

summary: Something that’s hard to communicate about Killing Eve when explaining the show imo is how colored by delight it is? Like full...
body: Something that’s hard to communicate about Killing Eve when explaining the show imo is how colored by delight it is? Like full of pleasure that despite the subject matter often isn’t really horrific at all? You’re like yeah it’s about an assassin and the new spy looking for her and like weaponizing femininity and you mention that it’s also funny but it doesn’t quite come across that delight is part of its essential makeup
